<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/1999-10-20.6.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-99/wa1020.htm#1850">Community Care</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/1999-10-20.6.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80136" speakername="Robert Brown (Glasgow) (LD)" spid="S1W-1881" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-99/wa1020.htm#1850">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive when it expects to make decisions on its response to the Royal Commission on Long Term Care.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/1999-10-20.6.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80167" speakername="Iain Gray" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-99/wa1020.htm#1850">

  <p>The recommendations in the Commission&#8217;s report cover a wide range of issues. We are continuing to consider them and will respond as soon as possible.</p>

</reply>


<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/1999-10-20.7.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-99/wa1020.htm#1850">Community Care</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/1999-10-20.7.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80136" speakername="Robert Brown (Glasgow) (LD)" spid="S1W-1882" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-99/wa1020.htm#1850">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive whether it has had discussions with Her Majesty&#8217;s Government on the implementation of the recommendations of the Royal Commission on Long Term Care.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/1999-10-20.7.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80167" speakername="Iain Gray" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-99/wa1020.htm#1850">

  <p>The Commission&#8217;s Report, <i>With Respect to Old Age,</i> makes wide-ranging recommendations on both devolved and reserved matters. The recommendations about social security matters and pensions are reserved to Westminster. The Scottish Executive is in regular contact with Her Majesty&#8217;s Government on a wide range of issues including the recommendations of the Royal Commission.</p>

</reply>


